The Ondo State Government (ODSG) has said it will provide relief materials to victims of last Saturday’s rainstorm that destroyed homes and public formations in Okitipupa and its environs. The deputy governor of the state, Mr Agboola Ajayi, said this when he visited Okitipupa and other communities affected by the rainstorm on Thursday. He said that the state government and the National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) would ensure the relief materials get to the victims soon. Ajayi was represented by the Permanent Secretary in the Deputy Governor’s Office, Mrs Desola Alabi. Other communities visited by the deputy governor include: Ajagba, llutitun, Okitipupa, lju-Odo, Asewele Oja, Asewele Korede and Oba-lle. Also, the state Commissioner for Education, Mr Femi Agagu, said the state government had begun the collation of homes and public institutions affected by the storm for quick intervention. Agagu called on the old students of the affected schools to come to their aid saying the destruction was massive. The Head of Operations of NEMA office in charge of Ekiti, Ondo and Osun states, Mr Tunde Adebiyi, described the incident as devastating. Also, the Vice Principal of Juwiri Comprehensive High School, Oke Ajagba, Mr Sunday Orilogbon, thanked the state government for the visit. Orilogbon appealed to the state government and concerned agencies to assist the victims on time. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 